uestmaster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Altrux Questmaster</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/24/02 11:52:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=321.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://personal.bhm.bellsouth.net/bhm/l/l/llid/EQ/altruxhat.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help me with a tactic on Bloodgills.</span><hr size=1> i found because of multiple reasons (newbies 'helping' and the tenddency they have to stop following and gate back to spawn) it was most efficent to kill them on site<br><br>lead with root, snare nuke me down<br><br>much easyer at 49, 1 IC and 1 lvl 34 ice nuke kills them, so root IC small nuke, i could do 4 on a bar of mana, their resists are very low <p>Illegal javascript event tags or url parameters detected.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urashakra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rashakra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/25/02 9:02:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=321.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.myezboard.com/projects/ezboard/ezboard_userimages/forsakenlords/images/selfpic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help me with a tactic on Bloodgills.</span><hr size=1> At 45, you want to slap on Levitate, Skin, and some sort of SoW/Jboot/Tboot.  Invis yerself and swim down to a pillar.  Target one and start swimming towards the surface.  As you get close, flux him and both should come.  Surface and run to the other pillar.  Since you're lev'd you'll go much faster than them.  <br><br>Get to the next pillar, hit ESC to clear target.  Swim straight down to the gobbies and spam your F8 key till you get a target... Then swim up and flux before you surface.  you now have 4 bloodgills.  I prefer to do a couple laps around them in the water to bunch them up and then run them to the dry land for AE fun.<br><br>If you start to only get one gob, my preferred method is to get one, next pillar, get 2nd, back to first pillar... get 3rd, back to second pillar... get last one... run to shore.<br><br>Hope this helps <p><BR><BR><img src=http://www.myezboard.com/projects/ezboard/ezboard_userimages/forsakenlords/images/sig.jpg><BR><A HREF=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=79455 target=new>Player Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=milaru>Milaru</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/25/02 9:12:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=321.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help me with a tactic on Bloodgills.</span><hr size=1> DON'T fight them underwater.  It's hard to get an XP rez in loio.<br><br>damn bard quest. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=80058" target="_blank"><img src="http://web.tampabay.rr.com/eqsite/Milaru.jpg" border="0"></a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgr